\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Assume the project is always worth trying:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\frac{1}{4}\left[\min\left\{ \pi_{0},\hat{\pi}\right\} \right]^{2}-\underline{w}>0
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Define 
\begin_inset Formula $\bar{v}_{ij}$
\end_inset

 as the value of the reservation payoff to an agent of type 
\begin_inset Formula $j$
\end_inset

 such that a principal of type 
\begin_inset Formula $i$
\end_inset

 makes zero expected profits under the optimal contract.
 And define 
\begin_inset Formula $\underline{v}_{ij}$
\end_inset

 as the lowest 
\begin_inset Formula $\bar{u}_{j}$
\end_inset

 for which the participation constraint binds.
 
