If an election changes the mission, may reduce productivity of bureaucracy
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
If private-sector opportunities improve 
\begin_inset Formula $\rightarrow$
\end_inset

 more high-powered incentives in bureaucracy
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Lack of innovation: In profit-oriented sector, any innovation that increases
 
\begin_inset Formula $\pi_{0}$
\end_inset

 will be adopted.
 However, in a mission-oriented organization, only innovations that increase
 
\begin_inset Formula $\pi_{i}+\theta_{ij}$
\end_inset

 will be adopted.
 If the innovation increases 
\begin_inset Formula $\pi_{i}$
\end_inset

 but decreases 
\begin_inset Formula $\theta_{ij}$
\end_inset

 it may not be adopted.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\end_deeper
