Teacher Performance Pay: Experimental Evidence from India
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout

}
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Frame
\begin_inset Argument 4
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
Muralidharan & Sundararaman 2011: Introduction
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Randomized evaluation of teacher performance pay
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Large scale experiment in Andhra Pradesh, India
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Can we really measure teacher performance?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Teacher incentive programs can backfire (multitasking, teaching to the test
 etc.)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
How should bonus contracts be set up? 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Are bonuses a cost-effective way to increase performance?
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Separator plain
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Frame
\begin_inset Argument 4
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
Muralidharan & Sundararaman 2011: Model
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Teachers do 2 tasks
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate
\begin_inset Formula $T_{1}$
\end_inset

: teaching using curricular best practices
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
\begin_inset Formula $T_{2}$
\end_inset

: activities to increase scores on exams (drills, teaching to the test,
 cheating)
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
\begin_inset Formula $t_{1}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $t_{2}$
\end_inset

 denote time allocated to these tasks.
 Human capital gains are 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
H=f_{1}t_{1}+f_{2}t_{2}+\varepsilon
\]

\end_inset

where 
\begin_inset Formula $f_{1}$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $f_{2}$
\end_inset

 are marginal products and 
\begin_inset Formula $\varepsilon$
\end_inset

 is noise outside teacher's control
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Planner cannot observe 
\begin_inset Formula $H$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $t_{1}$
\end_inset

 or 
\begin_inset Formula $t_{2}$
\end_inset

 but observes performance measure 
\begin_inset Formula $P$
\end_inset

 (e.g.
 test scores)
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
P=g_{1}t_{1}+g_{2}t_{2}+\phi
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Separator plain
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Frame
\begin_inset Argument 4
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
Muralidharan & Sundararaman 2011: Model
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Principal offers a wage contract depending on 
\begin_inset Formula $P$
\end_inset

: e.g.
 
\begin_inset Formula $w=s+bP$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Teacher's utility is
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
U=\mathbb{E}\left[w\right]-C\left(t_{1},t_{2};\bar{t}\right)
\]

\end_inset

where 
\begin_inset Formula $\bar{t}$
\end_inset

 is an effort norm.
 Teachers suffer a psychic cost if 
\begin_inset Formula $t_{1}+t_{2}<\bar{t}$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Optimal bonus 
\begin_inset Formula $b^{*}$
\end_inset

 depends on functional form of 
\begin_inset Formula $C$
\end_inset

, but when 
\begin_inset Formula $t_{1}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $t_{2}$
\end_inset

 are substitutes, easy to construct examples s.t.
 
\begin_inset Formula $b^{*}=0$
\end_inset

: better to accept the output generated by the norm 
\begin_inset Formula $\bar{t}$
\end_inset

 than to distort input allocation.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
But, if 
\begin_inset Formula $\bar{t}$
\end_inset

 is small, then gains from increasing effort can exceed costs of distorting
 effort.
 Plausible in India: Absenteeism is very high.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Moreover, if 
\begin_inset Formula $f_{1}/f_{2}$
\end_inset

 is not too much greater than 1, less substitution.
 Plausible in India: Tests are central to the system so best practice may
 be to teach to the test.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Separator plain
\end_inset


\end_layout

