\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Study urban property tax in Punjab, Pakistan (population 110 million)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Same tax setting as in Khan et al 2016.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
About 1/3 inspectors is transferred each year
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Inspectors care about where they are posted, the circles are very heterogeneous.
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Size: 90th %ile has 3x properties of 10th %ile
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Ease of collecting taxes, opportunities for corruption
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Amenities
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Current transfer process is opaque and subject to political influence, so
 limited use as incentive.
\end_layout

