\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
ask inspectors to rank all circles (average 10) in their district.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Told preferences would be used in treatments (incentive compatible to reveal
 true preferences) but before told treatment status
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Calculate the allocation that makes no inspector worse off, and no inspector
 or group of inspectors would want to deviate (Shapley & Scarf, 1974).
 15% of inspectors would move, and these individuals would move 30%iles
 up their preference ordering.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
15% relatively small, suggests that the incentive scheme will create both
 winners and losers.
\end_layout

