Leaver et al (2021): Motivation
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Recruiting good people, motivating and retaining them are central challenges
 for any organization with significant labor inputs
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Might Pay for Performance (P4P) be a good way of doing this? We know it
 can motivate teachers (Muralidharan & Sundararaman 2011)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Anti: 
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
crowd out pro-social mottivation
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
screen in the wrong people (Benabou & Tirole, 2003, 2006)
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Pro:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
classic contract theory (Lazear 2003)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
evidence from jobs with readily measurable output (Lazear 2000)
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Work in Rwanda to conduct the first RCT to test for these effects together.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
