Leaver et al (2021): Second Tier Randomization
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
After all the new teachers had been placed, all of the schools were randomized
 into either P4P (85 schools) or FW (79 schools)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
All teachers received the randomly assigned contract, both new and incumbents.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
P4P contract: top 20% of teachers receive FRw 100K ($136 
\begin_inset Formula $\sim$
\end_inset

 15% of annual salary)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Eligibility was equally weighted average of a) 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

pay for percentile
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

: Students' measured performance gains controling for student composition;
 b) teacher presence; c) lesson preparation; d) observed pedagogy
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
FW was bonus of FR2 20K for all teachers
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Potential worry: disappointment, so offered FRw 80K 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

retention bonus
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 to people who completed the year on top of P4P/FW
\end_layout

