\end_inset

The Costs of Patronage: Evidence from the British Empire
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout

}
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Frame
\begin_inset Argument 4
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
Xu 2017: Introduction
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Patronage has always been an important feature of the appointment of officials
 to public office.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
If principals have private information, patronage can be beneficial.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
But if it disincentivizes subordinates, it's detrimental.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
This project: Study impact of patronage on state performance in the Colonial
 Office of the British Empire.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Separator plain
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Frame
\begin_inset Argument 4
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout

\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Standard
\align center
\begin_inset Graphics
	filename pictures/Xu2017_1.png
	width 100text%

\end_inset


\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Separator plain
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Frame
\begin_inset Argument 4
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
Xu 2017: Context
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Study the Colonial Office.
 Founded in 1854 to administer 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

overseas possessions
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 At the peak of British colonialism, the bureaucracy spanned the globe,
 covering 1/5 of the world's land mass.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Identifying variation comes from two sources
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Ministerial turnover.
 The Colonial Office headed by the Secretary of State: a cabinet level political
 appointee.
 When the Prime Minister reshuffled the cabinet, or when there was an election,
 the connectedness of serving governors changed.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Changes in the appointment regime.
 The Secretary of State had discretion to appoint governors 1854-1930: the
 
\emph on
patronage
\emph default
 period.
 In 1930 replaced by a formal system of open recruitment, the 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

Magna Carta of the Colonial Service
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Separator plain
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Frame
\begin_inset Argument 4
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
Xu 2017: Data
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Digitized data to construct an individual-level personnel dataset on the
 Colonial Office
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Colonial Lists.
 Data on postings, backgrounds, and salaries of governors 18601966
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Blue Books 18211949.
 administrative statistics with detailed data on public finance (revenues,
 expenditures), demographics, trade and socio-economic statistic, and prices.
\end_layout

